<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>22-1707</num>
  <heading>“Gaming table” defined.</heading>
  <text>All games, devices, or contrivances at which money or any other thing shall be bet or wagered shall be deemed a gaming table within the meaning of §§ <cite path="§22-1704">22-1704</cite> to <cite path="§22-1706">22-1706</cite>; and the courts shall construe said sections liberally, so as to prevent the mischief intended to be guarded against.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 56-2-ch854" path="§868">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1331, ch. 854, § 868</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1973 Ed., § 22-1507.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Prior Codifications">1981 Ed., § 22-1507.</annotation>
    <annotation type="Cross References">Search warrants, see <cite path="§23-521">§ 23-521</cite> et seq.</annotation>
  </annotations>
</section>
